@NODE MAIN Skeleton

@{b}Skeleton 1.0@{ub}  Jörgen Grahn 1995-10-18

@{i}Note:  Browsing this AmigaGuide document will work well.@{ui}

When you start working on a new programming project, there are a lot of
things to set up:  compiler flags, makefile layout, revision control et
cetera.  Documentation, installation script and icons are needed if you
plan to release it as well.

This archive contains a skeleton or template for such a project, removing
many of the trivial decisions from the programmer, and hopefully allowing
her to concentrate on design, writing and programming.

